#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:5
msgid "CPU Build Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:8
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:10
msgid ""
"NumPy provides configuration options to optimize performance based on CPU "
"capabilities. These options allow you to specify which CPU features to "
"support, balancing performance, compatibility, and binary size. This "
"document explains how to use these options effectively across various CPU "
"architectures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:15
msgid "Key Configuration Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:17
msgid "NumPy uses several build options to control CPU optimizations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:19
msgid ""
"``cpu-baseline``: The minimum set of CPU features required to run the "
"compiled NumPy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:21
msgid ""
"Default: ``min`` (provides compatibility across a wide range of platforms)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:22
msgid ""
"If your target CPU doesn't support all specified baseline features, NumPy "
"will fail to load with a Python runtime error"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:24
msgid ""
"``cpu-baseline-detect``: controls detection of CPU baseline based on "
"compiler flags. Default value is ``auto`` that enables detection if ``-"
"march=`` or a similar compiler flag is used. The other possible values are "
"``enabled`` and ``disabled`` to respective enable or disable it "
"unconditionally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:29
msgid ""
"``cpu-dispatch``: Additional CPU features for which optimized code paths "
"will be generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:31
msgid "Default: ``max`` (enables all available optimizations)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:32
msgid ""
"At runtime, NumPy will automatically select the fastest available code path "
"based on your CPU's capabilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:34
msgid "``disable-optimization``: Completely disables all CPU optimizations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:36
msgid "Default: ``false`` (optimizations are enabled)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:37
msgid ""
"When set to ``true``, disables all CPU optimized code including dispatch, "
"SIMD, and loop unrolling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:38
msgid ""
"Useful for debugging, testing, or in environments where optimization causes "
"issues"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:40
msgid "These options are specified at build time via meson-python arguments::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:42
msgid ""
"pip install . -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-baseline=\"min\" -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-"
"dispatch=\"max\"\n"
"# or through spin\n"
"spin build -- -Dcpu-baseline=\"min\" -Dcpu-dispatch=\"max\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:46
msgid ""
"``cpu-baseline`` and ``cpu-dispatch`` can be set to specific :ref:`CPU "
"groups, features<opt-supported-features>`, or :ref:`special options <opt-"
"special-options>` that perform specific actions. The following sections "
"describe these options in detail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:50
msgid "Common Usage Scenarios"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:53
msgid "Building for Local Use Only"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:55
msgid "When building for your machine only and not planning to distribute::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:57
msgid ""
"python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-baseline=\"native\" -Csetup-args=-"
"Dcpu-dispatch=\"none\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:59
msgid ""
"This automatically detects and uses all CPU features available on your "
"machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:62
msgid ""
"A fatal error will be raised if ``native`` isn't supported by the host "
"platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:65
msgid "Excluding Specific Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:67
msgid ""
"You may want to exclude certain CPU features from the dispatched features::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:69
msgid ""
"# For x86-64: exclude all AVX-512 features\n"
"python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-dispatch=\"max -X86_V4\"\n"
"\n"
"# For ARM64: exclude SVE\n"
"python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-dispatch=\"max -SVE\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:76
msgid ""
"Excluding a feature will also exclude any successor features that are "
"implied by the excluded feature. For example, excluding ``X86_V4`` will "
"exclude ``AVX512_ICL`` and ``AVX512_SPR`` as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:81
msgid "Targeting Older CPUs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:83
msgid ""
"On ``x86-64``, by default the baseline is set to ``min`` which maps to "
"``X86_V2``. This unsuitable for older CPUs (before 2009) or old virtual "
"machines. To address this, set the baseline to ``none``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:87
msgid "python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-baseline=\"none\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:89
msgid ""
"This will create a build that is compatible with all x86 CPUs, but without "
"any manual optimizations or SIMD code paths for the baseline. The build will "
"rely only on dispatched code paths for optimization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:94
msgid "Targeting Newer CPUs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:96
msgid "Raising the baseline improves performance for two main reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:98
msgid "Dispatched kernels don't cover all code paths"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:99
msgid ""
"A higher baseline leads to smaller binary size as the compiler won't "
"generate code paths for excluded dispatched features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:101
msgid ""
"For CPUs from 2015 and newer, setting the baseline to ``X86_V3`` may be "
"suitable::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:103
msgid "python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-baseline=\"min+X86_V3\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:108
msgid "Supported CPU Features By Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:110
msgid ""
"NumPy supports optimized code paths for multiple CPU architectures. Below "
"are the supported feature groups for each architecture. The name of the "
"feature group can be used in the build options ``cpu-baseline`` and ``cpu-"
"dispatch``."
msgstr ""

