msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:327
msgid "Usage And Behaviors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:330
msgid "Case Insensitivity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:332
msgid "CPU features and options are case-insensitive::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:334
msgid "python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-dispatch=\"X86_v4\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:337
msgid "Mixing Features across Architectures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:339
msgid "You can mix features from different architectures::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:341
msgid "python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-baseline=\"X86_V4 VSX4 SVE\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:344
msgid "Order Independence"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:346
msgid "The order of specified features doesn't matter::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:348
msgid ""
"python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-dispatch=\"SVE X86_V4 x86_v3\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:351
msgid "Separators"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:353
msgid "You can use spaces or commas as separators::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:355
msgid ""
"# All of these are equivalent\n"
"python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-dispatch=\"X86_V2 X86_V4\"\n"
"python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-dispatch=X86_V2,X86_V4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:360
msgid "Feature Combination"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:362
msgid ""
"Features specified in options are automatically combined with all implied "
"features::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:364
msgid "python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-baseline=X86_V4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:366
msgid "Equivalent to::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:368
msgid ""
"python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-baseline=\"X86_V2 X86_V3 X86_V4\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:371
msgid "Baseline Overlapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:373
msgid ""
"Features specified in ``cpu-baseline`` will be excluded from the ``cpu-"
"dispatch`` features, along with their implied features, but without "
"excluding successor features that imply them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:376
msgid ""
"For instance, if you specify ``cpu-baseline=\"X86_V4\"``, it will exclude "
"``X86_V4`` and its implied features ``X86_V2`` and ``X86_V3`` from the ``cpu-"
"dispatch`` features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:380
msgid "Compile-time Detection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:382
msgid ""
"Specifying features to ``cpu-dispatch`` or ``cpu-baseline`` doesn't "
"explicitly enable them. Features are detected at compile time, and the "
"maximum available features based on your specified options will be enabled "
"according to toolchain and platform support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:386
msgid ""
"This detection occurs by testing feature availability in the compiler "
"through compile-time source files containing common intrinsics for the "
"specified features. If both the compiler and assembler support the feature, "
"it will be enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:390
msgid ""
"For example, if you specify ``cpu-dispatch=\"AVX512_ICL\"`` but your "
"compiler doesn't support it, the feature will be excluded from the build. "
"However, any implied features will still be enabled if they're supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:398
msgid "Platform differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:400
msgid ""
"Some exceptional conditions force us to link some features together when it "
"come to certain compilers or architectures, resulting in the impossibility "
"of building them separately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:403
msgid "These conditions can be divided into two parts, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:405
msgid "**Architectural compatibility**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:407
msgid ""
"The need to align certain CPU features that are assured to be supported by "
"successive generations of the same architecture, some cases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:410
msgid ""
"On ppc64le ``VSX(ISA 2.06)`` and ``VSX2(ISA 2.07)`` both imply one another "
"since the first generation that supports little-endian mode is ``Power-8(ISA "
"2.07)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:412
msgid ""
"On AArch64 ``NEON NEON_FP16 NEON_VFPV4 ASIMD`` implies each other since they "
"are part of the hardware baseline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:415
#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:479
msgid "For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:417
msgid ""
"# On ARMv8/A64, specify NEON is going to enable Advanced SIMD\n"
"# and all predecessor extensions\n"
"python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-baseline=neon\n"
"# which is equivalent to\n"
"python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=-Dcpu-baseline=\"neon neon_fp16 "
"neon_vfpv4 asimd\""
msgstr ""

